<% snippet = capture do %>
<button>Primary Button</button>
<button class="button-secondary">Secondary Button</button>
<button class="button-outline">Outline Button</button>
<button class="button-outline-secondary">Secondary Outline Button</button>
<button class="button-small">Small Button</button>
<button class="button-outline-secondary button-small">Small Button</button>
<button disabled>Disabled Button</button>
<button class="button-outline" disabled>Disabled Outline Button</button>

/* Change color */
.context .button {
  @include button-color($background-color, $text-color);
}
<% end %>

<div id="buttons" class="style-guide-section">
  <div class="style-guide-lead">
    <h2>Buttons</h2>

    <p>There are two styles of buttons used on the soludis website: primary and secondary.</p>

    <p>A "button" is considered any of the following:</p>

    <pre>.button,
    button,
    input[type="button"],
    input[type="reset"],
    input[type="submit"]</pre>

    <p>When wanting to use the secondary style, simply add <code>class="button-secondary"</code>.</p>

    <p>If you need to tweak a button's color (if you were adding one to a different colored background, for example), you can use the <code>button-color</code> mixin.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="style-guide-result">
    <div class="input-wrapper">
      <button>Primary Button</button>
      <button class="button-secondary">Secondary Button</button>
    </div>
    <div class="input-wrapper">
      <button class="button-outline">Outline Button</button>
      <button class="button-outline-secondary">Secondary Outline Button</button>
    </div>
    <div class="input-wrapper">
      <button class="button-small">Small Button</button>
      <button class="button-outline-secondary button-small">Small Button</button>
    </div>
    <div class="input-wrapper">
      <button disabled>Disabled Button</button>
      <button class="button-outline" disabled>Disabled Outline Button</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="style-guide-code">
    <pre><%= escape_once snippet %></pre>
  </div>
</div>
